    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 35 @ 2023/2024",
    "Question": {
      "content": "An electric device with resistance R = 75 Ω, is operated from a source having voltage V = 240 V. Find the electrical power of the device?",
      "type": "subJective",
      "options": []
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "768 W"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>Electrical power is given by\\( P =\\frac{V^2}{R}\\), where\\( V = 240\\,\\text{V}\\) and\\( R = 75\\,\\Omega\\). Thus,\\( P =\\frac{240^2}{75} =\\frac{57600}{75} = 768\\,\\text{W}\\). Alternatively, using\\( P = IV\\) and\\( I =\\frac{V}{R} =\\frac{240}{75} = 3.2\\,\\text{A}\\),\\( P = 240\\times 3.2 = 768\\,\\text{W}\\).</p>"
    },
    "topic": [
      "Electrical Power",
      "Ohm's Law",
      "DC Circuits",
      "Electric Potential",
      "Electrical Resistance"
    ]
